SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 675
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to congratulate Andrew Johnson Bank on the
occasion of its fiftieth anniversary.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should recognize
those dynamic financial institutions whose contributions have been vital to the economic life of
their respective communities; and
WHEREAS, Andrew Johnson Bank, a stalwart institution of the East Tennessee banking
community, is celebrating its fiftieth anniversary of providing outstanding financial services to the
people of Greeneville and beyond; and
WHEREAS, originally chartered in 1975 as City and County Bank, the institution
embraced its local heritage in 1980 when it rebranded as Andrew Johnson Bank, following a
community-wide naming contest that honored the seventeenth president of the United States
and Greeneville's most famous citizen; and
WHEREAS, in 2002, Andrew Johnson Bank moved its headquarters into a landmark
three-story building in downtown Greeneville, which was constructed in 1888 by Colonel John
H. Doughty, the great-grandfather of then-CEO Bill Hickerson; this historic structure, now listed
on the National Register of Historic Places, reflects the bank's deep roots and commitment to
the local community; and
WHEREAS, Bill Hickerson served as CEO from 1979 until his retirement in 2017,
guiding the bank with steady vision for thirty-nine years; under his leadership, Andrew Johnson
Bank grew from a modest institution with $10 million in assets and a single location into a
dynamic regional presence with $360 million in assets and seven locations; and
SJR0675
011489
- 1 -

WHEREAS, since 2018, Paige Hull has admirably served as CEO, continuing the bank's
tradition of integrity and innovation; in her seven-year tenure, the bank has flourished to more
than $600 million in assets and expanded its footprint to eight locations; and
WHEREAS, today, Andrew Johnson Bank stands as a full-service commercial bank with
over 100 dedicated employees, proudly serving clients in four Tennessee counties; with the
guiding motto "Helping Friends is Our Business," the bank exemplifies neighborly service and
community investment; and
WHEREAS, as Andrew Johnson Bank celebrates five decades of trusted leadership and
unwavering community focus, it is most appropriate to commend its enduring success, proud
history, and ongoing contributions to the financial well-being of Tennesseans; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate the leadership, board
members, and employees of Andrew Johnson Bank on the occasion of the institution's fiftieth
anniversary, commend their unflagging commitment to quality and integrity, and extend to them
our best wishes for much continued success in the future.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
